# Design System Rules

## Purpose

This file defines the standards for establishing and maintaining a design system for web-based user interfaces. These rules apply **only to systems with graphical web interfaces** (web applications, dashboards, portals). CLI-only and API-only systems do not require a design system, though they may benefit from one if they expose a web management interface.

> **AI Instruction**: These rules are **conditional** — they activate only when the Vision Document Section 4 identifies Web, Dashboard, or Mobile as a primary interface. If the system is CLI-only or API-only, skip this file. If a design system is applicable, load this file during Phase 2b (UX/Interaction Design) and reference it during all frontend implementation stages.

---

## When to Apply Design System Rules

### Rule DS-001: Applicability Gate

Evaluate the Vision Document Section 4 (Interface and Interaction Preferences):

| Condition | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Interfaces include Web, Dashboard, or Mobile | Apply all rules in this file |
| Interfaces include CLI only | Skip this file entirely |
| Interfaces include API only | Skip this file; apply IXD-011 through IXD-013 from `interaction-design.mdc` |
| Hybrid (API + Web admin portal) | Apply to the web portal component only |

Document the applicability decision in the UX Principles document.

---

## Design Token System

### Rule DS-002: Token-First Design

All visual properties (colors, typography, spacing, shadows, radii) are expressed as tokens before being applied in components. Never hardcode visual values in component definitions.

```
Level 1: Primitive tokens (raw values)
  --color-blue-500: #3B82F6;
  --font-size-16: 16px;
  --space-4: 4px;

Level 2: Semantic tokens (purpose-driven aliases)
  --color-action-primary: var(--color-blue-500);
  --text-size-body: var(--font-size-16);
  --space-component-gap: var(--space-4);

Level 3: Component tokens (component-specific overrides)
  --button-primary-bg: var(--color-action-primary);
  --card-body-size: var(--text-size-body);
```

Components reference Level 2 (semantic) or Level 3 (component) tokens only — never Level 1 directly.

### Rule DS-003: Color System Requirements

The color system must define:

| Token Category | Required Tokens |
|---------------|----------------|
| Brand | Primary, Secondary |
| Semantic | Success, Warning, Error, Info |
| Neutral | Background (page, surface, overlay), Border, Text (primary, secondary, disabled, inverse) |
| Interactive | Action (default, hover, active, disabled), Focus ring |

**Accessibility requirements**:
- Text on background: minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Large text (18pt+ or 14pt+ bold) on background: minimum 3:1
- Interactive components and focus indicators: minimum 3:1
- Never rely on color alone to convey information

### Rule DS-004: Typography Scale

Define a type scale based on a consistent ratio (e.g., Major Third = 1.25, Perfect Fourth = 1.333):

| Role | Token | Example Size | Usage |
|------|-------|-------------|-------|
| Display | `--text-display` | 48px | Hero headings only |
| Heading 1 | `--text-h1` | 32px | Page title |
| Heading 2 | `--text-h2` | 24px | Section title |
| Heading 3 | `--text-h3` | 20px | Subsection title |
| Body Large | `--text-body-lg` | 18px | Lead paragraph |
| Body | `--text-body` | 16px | Default body text |
| Body Small | `--text-body-sm` | 14px | Supporting text, labels |
| Caption | `--text-caption` | 12px | Image captions, footnotes |
| Code | `--text-code` | 14px | Monospace for code |

Define line height, font weight, and letter spacing for each role.

### Rule DS-005: Spacing System

Use a base unit (4px or 8px) to generate a consistent spacing scale:

```
--space-1: 4px    (hairline)
--space-2: 8px    (tight)
--space-3: 12px   
--space-4: 16px   (base unit — most common)
--space-5: 20px   
--space-6: 24px   (comfortable)
--space-8: 32px   (spacious)
--space-10: 40px  
--space-12: 48px  (section gap)
--space-16: 64px  
--space-24: 96px  (page section)
```

Components use spacing tokens only. `margin: 13px` is prohibited; `margin: var(--space-3)` is correct.

