## Component Library

### Rule DS-006: Component Classification

Classify components by reusability level:

| Level | Name | Description | Examples |
|-------|------|-------------|----------|
| Atoms | Primitive UI elements | Cannot be broken down further | Button, Input, Label, Icon |
| Molecules | Simple groups of atoms | Single clear function | Form Field (Label + Input + Error), Card Header |
| Organisms | Complex groups | Distinct section of interface | Navigation Bar, Data Table, Form |
| Templates | Page layouts | Arrange organisms in a layout | Dashboard Layout, Settings Layout |

### Rule DS-007: Component Documentation Requirements

Every component in the library must document:

1. **Purpose**: One sentence describing what the component is for
2. **Variants**: All visual and behavioral variations (e.g., Button: primary, secondary, destructive, disabled)
3. **Props/Parameters**: All configurable inputs with types, defaults, and descriptions
4. **States**: Every interactive state (default, hover, focus, active, disabled, loading, error)
5. **Accessibility**: ARIA roles, keyboard interactions, screen reader behavior
6. **Examples**: At least one usage example per variant
7. **Do / Don't**: At least one usage anti-pattern

### Rule DS-008: Component Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Component name | PascalCase | `Button`, `DataTable`, `NavigationBar` |
| CSS class / token name | kebab-case | `button-primary`, `nav-bar--collapsed` |
| Variant modifier | BEM modifier (`--`) | `button--destructive`, `input--error` |
| State class | State prefix | `is-loading`, `is-disabled`, `has-error` |
| Component file | kebab-case | `button.tsx`, `data-table.tsx` |

### Rule DS-009: Interaction States

Every interactive component must have designs for all applicable states:

| State | Requirement |
|-------|------------|
| Default | Base appearance |
| Hover | Visual change that signals clickability |
| Focus | Visible focus ring (min 2px, 3:1 contrast) |
| Active / Pressed | Visual confirmation of interaction |
| Disabled | Visually distinct; not interactive; `aria-disabled` |
| Loading | Spinner or skeleton; prevents re-interaction |
| Error | Error indicator (color + icon + text); not just color |
| Success | Confirmation indicator |

