## Pattern Library

### Rule DS-010: Required Interaction Patterns

Define standard patterns for these common interactions. Once defined, they must be applied consistently across the system:

| Pattern | Required When |
|---------|--------------|
| Form validation | Any form with user input |
| Loading state | Any async operation visible to user |
| Empty state | Any list or data view that can be empty |
| Error state | Any page, component, or form that can fail |
| Confirmation dialog | Any destructive or irreversible action |
| Notification / toast | System-generated feedback (success, error, warning) |
| Pagination | Any list that can exceed 25 items |
| Search and filter | Any list with > 10 expected items |

### Rule DS-011: Iconography

Icons must come from a single, consistent source. Mixing icon sets is prohibited.

Requirements:
- Choose one icon library and document it in the design system
- All icons have text alternatives (aria-label or visually-hidden text)
- Icon size follows the spacing scale
- Icon color uses semantic color tokens (never hardcoded hex)
- Interactive icons have all required states (hover, focus, active, disabled)

