## Design-to-Code Handoff

### Rule DS-012: Token Synchronization

Design tokens defined in the design tool (Figma, Sketch, etc.) must be exported and committed to the codebase. The codebase token file is the single source of truth at build time.

Synchronization process:
1. Design tokens are updated in the design tool
2. Tokens are exported (Style Dictionary, Theo, or equivalent)
3. The exported file replaces the codebase token file
4. A design system changelog entry is added

### Rule DS-013: Component Spec Completeness

Before a component is handed to engineering for implementation, its documentation (per DS-007) must be complete for all planned variants. Incomplete component specs are returned to design.

---

## Design System Evolution

### Rule DS-014: Design System Change Process

Changes to the design system (new tokens, new components, breaking changes) follow the same L1–L4 classification as architecture changes (EVO-001):

| Change Type | Classification | Required Process |
|-------------|--------------|-----------------|
| Token value adjustment (no structure change) | L1 | Direct update |
| New token | L2 | Lightweight ADR |
| New component | L2 | Lightweight ADR + component spec |
| Component variant added | L2 | Update component spec |
| Breaking: component renamed or removed | L3 | Full ADR + migration guide |
| Breaking: token renamed or restructured | L3 | Full ADR + migration guide |

### Rule DS-015: Deprecation Policy

Deprecated components and tokens:
- Remain available for 2 release cycles before removal
- Are marked with a `@deprecated` annotation and migration note
- Are listed in the design system changelog under "Deprecated"
- Trigger a console warning in development mode when used

